description: A single dad and his baby daughter wander through a fantastic version of our world on a constant search for diapers, waffles and a place (and the free time!) to poop. While trying to live off his ability to write poetry scrolls, their obstacles include nightmares, judgmental parents, swaddling contests, and combative assassins. A personal allegory for the trials of being a new parent.
